reviews_data.review_text:
I eat here regularly for brunch. The food has great flavor and I am impressed by the presentation as well. Some of my favorite dishes are the frijoles, baked apple grain bowl, pancakes, and Spanish omelette. The shakshuka is great too.

It’s in a quiet neighborhood and it’s usually easy to find street parking. The only thing that would make this place better is if they offered espresso drinks!
Chicken and blueberry waffle was delicious!

Delicious food, friendly people, convenient neighborhood location... My only regret is not trying it sooner. If you ever get the chance to attend one of their wine dinners, do not sleep on the opportunity. One of the best meals I've had!
Best pancakes I have ever had! Loved this place! We had to wait in line to order on a Saturday afternoon but it was worth it!

Chicken and the egg is so dank.  The only thing they lose at is it's always busy, slow to get food.  Then if you want a refill on coffee, you have to wait through the line just to get a refill.  This process needs to be fixed... It's like a manufactured bottleneck to slow down getting a refill.
We love this place and travel 2 hours for a meal or two.  We’ll worth the trip effort
I don’t normally give reviews, but this one deserves it. Food was incredible. Local shop you think “more of an atmosphere vibe”. But this place had the vibes & the food. 10/10 will be back
Love this place! Good food, friendly, and very affordable. Busy on the weekends so give more time than you think you need.
The food was excellent 👌

Food was okay. Service was the worst we have seen in Charlotte/anywhere. After asking if they had iced coffee, the guy behind the counter said "we don't serve snotty drinks, you can go somewhere else for that". Seemed as if he was angry that we were asking for something breakfast related. When we were finished ordering he said "since you showed up late, your food will be 45 minutes" At this point we thought we were on a hidden camera show. Rude guy, not cool, won't be back.
Great food and amazing staff

What can I say about this one in a million place to enjoy your morning coffee or dine in!
Best hosts and amazing chef!
My morning falafel wrap which was a special order. Please keep preserving the Authentic places like these♥️
One of the best brunch places in Charlotte. Make sure you go early on Sundays , otherwise you might end up waiting for an hour to get your order.
Why choose? This ain't a riddle. "The Chicken & the Egg"

Food was excellent!  The grain bowl was AMAZING! I want to score it lower so it’s not so busy, and I am choosing to live within my integrity and score it what it truly deserves: 5 stars across the board!

I live in Charlotte, LOVE breakfast, and am committed to finding the best b-fast place.  This, my friends, is it.  Every item on the menu is SOO exquisitely crafted, extremely fresh, and simply cannot be beaten.  My parents visiting from out of town asked to go here 3 days in a row.  Even the basic items, like the eggs and pancakes, are like nothing I’ve tasted before.  Truly a Charlotte GEM!
Man this place is such an awesome little spot. Fantastic food at a great price.

This restaurant is on the corner of an unassuming neighborhood. When you walk in you are greeted by the most friendly man operating the register. He recommended a few of his favorites and joked around with us a bit while taking our order. Definitely a place where the people are the focus.

The food is what brings it all together however. I think my friend had a religious experience when eating the shrimp and grits. Highly recommend stopping by. If it's a nice day, sit outside and enjoy the community that is all around you.

Food was really good and highly recommend the baked goods as well. Staff was friendly and they handled the breakfast rush like it was nothing. This place looks kinda unassuming but the little kitchen back there whips up some DELICIOUS food. Highly recommend 👌
Incredible cookies

Genuinely one of if not my favorite restaurants in CLT. Anything you get here will be amazing, but their brunch is especially to die for. Hidden gem seated in a neighborhood that you need to try if you’re in the area.
Wonderful breakfast - had the Spanish migas and nearly polished the bowl. The drip coffee was outstanding. We enjoyed the counter service and sitting outside in the quiet neighborhood.
This is a great neighborhood restaurant. Expect to wait it is worth it.
I love places like this that are tucked away in a neighborhood. We visited for a late breakfast and loved the atmosphere and menu.
We had five different dishes and they were all delicious. I would highly recommend this cute place. We even walked around the neighborhood afterwards.
Best brunch in Charlotte!
The Shakshukah is delicious.
Food was okay/somewhat overpriced for what you get. It also took us over an hour to be served after ordering.
Everything I have tried is amazing.
Great little place in the midst of a neighborhood. The Chicken and Egg was awesome, my kids love their breakfast burritos
Great food and great service
Great local brunch spot!! I like to come here for a quiet breakfast with family or friends and it is always so cozy!!
The service was quite limited, and we waited an unusually long time for our food. When my meal finally arrived, it was decent, but the overall experience left much to be desired.
Every single person needs to come here. This is the best food I’ve had in NC by far. It’s genuinely a hidden gem, the service is good and the food is incredible and fresh and served beautifully!

I'm giving this a "round up" 4- I'd say it's closer to 3.5-3.75. I came here with my friends on Friday around 7pm; it's one of their go-to spots. Very cute all around, bright, open inviting. They have beer, wine, pastries, and a good food menu. We opted to split a pineapple orange juice mimosa carafe ($25 weekday special). I ordered the beef empanadas and my friends had an order of that as well along with the calamari. Took a bit longer than expected for our carafe to come out, but the food followed shortly after. I'm not picky about the bubbly brands/flavors, but my one pet peeve is when mimosa/champagne isn't chilled, and that was the case with our carafe. I hadn't had pineapple OJ before, so I enjoyed that blend, but I really wish that it had the crisp/chill to it. The empanadas were very tasty, but seemed slightly underfilled (very airy, maybe 50% filled with meat). I enjoyed the dipping sauce though. This is a solid spot that I would return to to try some other stuff on the menu, but I do think there are areas for improvement!

I don't know what happened. Between the SEC biscuit and pancake platter there was enough grease to oil up a car. So, right off the bat everything was hard to eat. The pancakes were...deep fried?? That would have been nice to know beforehand. Everything was just lacking. I think I'm 0/2 now here. The gentleman taking orders was very nice and kept the line moving.

every time i eat here i enjoy it! i love bringing friends here that are visiting. yet to have something bad on the menu, but i also like to order the same thing every time. get the house made hot sauce. it’s unmatched.

Amazing food and service!
They have created a new category of quality and service that most will not be able to duplicate!

After sitting at a filthy table with no one checking on us or bringing our drinks the server delivered our food to a filthy table with plates stacked up and empty glasses, chewed up steak on the plates and tables. I asked him to clear it several times as our food is coming out of the kitchen. Then he had an attitude like we are bothering him by asking him to wipe down the mess and get the chewed up meat off the table and flung towards us as he’s wiping aggressively. The food average at best and the service is horrible. Cute idea though for the right staff.

The food here is fantastic. Easily one of the best places for brunch here in Charlotte. However, because the place is small, sometimes you will have to wait a little for them to bring out your food, so please be patient with the staff. If it is busy, I usually walk to a local coffee shop since there are multiple around this area, and it takes only a few minutes to get a coffee and return. By the time I get my coffee, my food is ready. I highly recommend this place!
The elevated sandwich in a rekaxed atmosphere

What could be worth 15 mins of standing in line to place an order and an hour after that waiting for food? Nothing!

Also, good luck finding a table.
Never misses

Great little cafe bakery in a cute neighborhood. The outdoor seating was great but the interior seating was a bit meh.
Everything we ordered was really good, and someone in my group raved that the coffee cake muffin was the best muffin he ever had.

I absolutely love everything about this local family-owned gem!! 🤩 They are nestled into the cutest little house, right in the heart of Noda. This is the perfect spot to grab a quick sweet treat or an incredibly delicious chef-driven meal.
They even grow a lot of their produce on property!!
I’ve taken a number of people here and they are all always blown away by how incredibly delicious and thoughtful the meals are. The menu is well rounded and touches all parts of the globe. It is extremely user-friendly for vegetarians and offer a couple of solid options for vegans.
Here are some of the meals that my guest and I have rave about: Spanish Migas, patatas bravas, Shukshuka, ALL of the Tartines, Boxty Browns, ALL of the pastries, Frijoles de la Olla. 🤗

Another favorite thing about this spot is that they are fixtures in the local Charlotte community and bring together local farmers and vendors for there weekly farmers market taking place every Thursday. You can even pick up your CSA share at the market.
And service is always on point!!
Had a great sandwich.  Neat spot.  Check it out
Chicken and the egg was phenomenal

Just don’t.
Unless you want to spend your entire brunch in line to order AND again anytime you need a coffee refill. I’m talking 45 mins to order, every time. Seriously, go to the company store instead.
Bless that man’s heart, yall need to do better by your coworkers and get him some backup.

Really disappointed with Local Loaf. We went in for the first time, placed our order and sat down. We then waited for nearly 30 minutes watching everyone around us get their food. When we asked, turns out they never put our order in. I completely understand these things happen, but their response of not apologizing or attempting to fix the mistake is why I’m writing this review. They refunded us but didn’t seem the least bit concerned or worried that we wasted half an hour with a baby for food that was never coming.
Our first time here and really enjoyed the food. The flavor was really good.

Was here with a friend for breakfast. Neither of us had been here before, hadn’t even heard of it until this week. Arrived 9am on a Wednesday and had no trouble finding street parking. Quaint little place on a corner, tucked in a residential area (wish there were more of these in Charlotte). No line for counter service, plenty of tables available. Nice, friendly guy running the front of house, interesting menu. We had the Spanish Migas and the Bubble & Squeak Boxty Benny. Both were excellent, well seasoned and cooked to perfection, but the Spanish Migas is what will bring us back. Not really any service once our food was delivered, but we were ok with that, as we were talking and catching up. Pretty sure we could’ve waved somebody down for more coffee or water if we’d tried. We will be back, and we’ll let our friends and family know about this place.
Great spot for beakfast
The breakfast was one of the best we've ever had. Expect a line before ordering and finding a table.

Recently attended a beer dinner at Local Loaf. The space is quaint and quiet. Adam (the chef) shared why he chose each dish pairing with beer, which was very thoughtful. I was blown away by the small details in each dish.
Wet very good food!  Very popular and for good reason! Coffee was great too!
Got the eggs Benedict and it was amazing. Also got a huge Snickerdoodle cookie 🍪
Great food.

As someone who prefers local restaurants over chain restaurants, I was looking forward to trying them out. Being that it was Sunday, I expected a wait but what transpired was absolutely ridiculous. The line was long, again expected, but moved at a decent rate. My husband found seating while I stood in line and it took about 20-25 to order our food. Once seated, I observed the average time it took for people to get their food based on who was in line with me. It started off pretty normal until I realized that the group that was in line behind us had received their food before us. At that point I asked for an update on our order. That waiter never returned with an update. Shortly after my husband received his food. 10 minutes later my daughter and I still hadn’t received ours. Another waiter then informed me that “something went wrong with your pancakes” and apologized for the wait. At this point, waiting an hour and a half for a pretty simple breakfast order left us both with a headache. Not how I hoped to start my Sunday.

$12 dollars for a Cuban. It was my first time going there, so I didn't look at the sandwich until I got home, and this is what I got for $12. Half a sandwich! Absolutely ridiculous! Won't get my business again!
Very comfortable and welcomng neighborhood vibe.  The food is great and the owners are easy to get to know.

Breakfast is AMAZING. Generous portion sizes. Chefs are super friendly.
The wine dinners are so much fun and a fantastic value.

First time here and the food was surprisingly very complex and delicious! We did have to wait around 15 min for a table to open up but it made the 30 min wait for food go by faster. Staff is super friendly. The place is kind of small and I would recommend that they use more 2 person tables instead of 4 person tables to allow more parties to seat. Overall, great spot.

Local loaf is a gem! We ordered the Italian sandwich, lobster dip, chicken fried steak biscuit, and breakfast sandwich. Everything was fresh and cooked to perfection. The only thing I need to add is everything is cooked to order, so if you order anything complex, you will be waiting to get your dish while the people at your table are already eating or finished. But the food was worth waiting for! Will be back for more!!
Great food!!! It took a while to come out but it was definitely worth it. Plus we enjoyed the atmosphere. The bagged fresh English muffins are SO good. Must buy!
The workers were super nice and the food was great. We got the pancakes and the biscuits and gravy. Gravy was way more sausage than gravy but still good. Will visit here again.

Visited for brunch after looking for a "new" place to visit. The restaurant was nice and was snuggled in a very "quiet" community.  Parking was a challenge, and so was seating. I tried to make reservations, but the restaurant did not allow this feature. However,  with limited parking and seating, this would be a good option to help with traffic in and around the restaurant .

The wait for a table was not so bad, but the wait to receive our order was extremely long. ( People that came after our party were being served, but it was random dishes at these tables. Not everyone at the table was served.)

*Please note that I pay close attention to service and where we are in reference to the order that we come into a restaurant.

Once our food arrived, I was disappointed with my Shrimp and Grits. The dish was very salty.  The eggs with the pancake breakfast were also very salty.  The pancakes and bacon were okay, but the pancakes were cooked very well and mostly hard rather than fluffy. The Spanish Omelet tasted very good. The Omelet was fluffy, not too much salt, and loaded with peppers,  onions, and tomatoes.

The most disappointing thing about our experience was the poor service. No one came to refill our coffee (unless we asked) or ever came to check on us after we "finally" received our food. I would like to think that this experience was due to them being short staffed, but due to the entire dining experience, I will not return.
A little Diamond in the rough.

Visiting area and tried it on a whim. No more breakfast whims for me LOL.
Coffee tasted bitter. Wifey had a Benedict and I had a Croque.  She had mild food poisoning a few hours later and I was bloated.  She noticed that "sauce" on the dish tasted like mayo.  If it was, mayo is a crapshoot to use since it spoils unpredictably.  It was the only thing we had that morning, so something there got us to that point 🤒.  What a shame.
Brunch is delish! Order at the counter and some staff to help bus tables. Chill vibe overall
Cool little place and great food.

By far one of the best breakfast/brunch spots in Charlotte. Have loved everything I have got from them & the prices are beyond reasonable. Service is always great & consistent too! Highly recommend all the baked goods as well. The cookies are to die for.
Went to try the French toast with my daughter and they said “we got tired of making it” but it’s coming back…
Great food
Food was great, nice atmosphere. Chicken fried steak. Got a can of seasonal beer from the fridge. Low capacity/long wait but maybe just don't go Sunday brunch

The employees were very sweet and the service was fast, but the coffee cake muffin, cheese grits, and croque monsieur were not the best. The croque was more like texas toast with a lot of thick sauce. However the location was super cute and everyone was very nice!

We ordered from them several times & good is really good.
My husband & I had to write this review today cause we pre ordered online & even if the chef was sick his wife made it a mission to honor the order early this morning after Thanksgiving.
Kudos to you guys!!!!
We’ll always come back ..much respect for your commitment to your trade, biz and life.

Went for brunch this past Sunday and was extremely excited to try this place. Looking at all the reviews we were ready to wait a while for the food which we didn’t mind doing at all. We ordered our meals just fine and sat down to wait. The food took the 45 minutes they told us it would but this is when things started to go downhill. The guy at the front counter rung in one of the meals wrong so they brought out something completely different from what we told the guy. We didn’t really mind because the meal was actually a menu item we had been debating on ordering. It tasted really good and we liked it but the way the situation was handled was very poor. They didn’t really offer to make us the right meal and really tried to convince us to just take the messed up order so they didn’t have to fix their mistake.

On top of that the other meal we ordered “the box Benny” wasn’t so great as it was practically saltless or very under salted. If they had added some salt the meal would’ve been perfect. Will still be coming back to give this place another try though.

Everything about here is amazing. I love the set up because it is so cute and intimate, plus you can see the magic in the kitchen. The food was amazingly put together and seasoned to perfection.  And the service was everything. I definitely will be returning.
HANDS DOWN the best chicken and waffles I’ve had in my life! Great music and the friendliest face when we walked in and ordered. Will be back 100%
Speechless. Just go there and remember my comment. Speechless.
The food, service and atmosphere was all so perfect! Being here felt like being at home, but better! These aren’t cooks, but amazing chefs! We will definitely be visiting this establishment again!

reviews_data.review_text: This is a fantastic breakfast spot! I brought in my friends from out of town, and we all loved the friendly atmosphere and wonderful food. I had the Spanish Migas bowl, and it was definitely one of the best breakfasts I’ve had since I’ve been in Charlotte.

Wow, delicious breakfast!!! My husband had the Spanish migas. It had unique flavors that perfectly complimented eachother and made for a delicious mouth watering experience. I ordered the breakfast burrito and replaced the sweet potatoes with regular potatoes. It was so flavorful and delicious too!  The kids' breakfasts were cooked perfectly and the sausage was so flavorful. Even though the sausage had a little spice they kept eating it. I love this place and will definitely come back when I pass through again. Wish I took pictures before it was half eaten. They were beautifully presented. The service was friendly and great. Come here and enjoy!!!
Loved the food!
Best shrimp and grits of my life.

Updated review: The chef came out to speak with us and explained the long wait. We were visiting from out of town and didn’t realize it would be this long. It was over an hour for our breakfast and when it finally came out they brought 2/4 of our plates and we waited another 15 mins for the other two. Service got better and we also spoke with our server who was very nice and accommodating. As an apology the chef sent us home with bake at home cookies and can’t wait to try them.

Chef, I wrote this review before we spoke. The breakfast was delicious and everyone loved the pancake. We appreciate you taking the time to talk with us and sending cookies home as well. I don’t know why you mentioned us yelling and cussing at the FOH staff? That never happened and we did politely ask for an update twice and also very friendly with our server. Sorry for the misunderstanding and that you have to deal with a small kitchen. How are we suppose to know? We did not expect a fairytale and perfect service. We would be happy to come back again. Maybe on a week day next time.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Great talking with you, honestly felt you totally understood the situation and you seemed very nice but thanks for actually not understanding at all.

((For anyone reading this post. Yes we have a very small kitchen and a decent size menu, that's ALL made to order and honestly don't plan on changing that anytime soon. Saturdays and Sundays in Charlotte are very busy for ANY GOOD RESTAURANT, SERVING GOOD FOOD.  WE GET THIS A LOT, HONESTLY, WE ARE VERY VERY BUSY ON SATURDAYS AND SUNDAYS. We are not a little fairy tale place where everything is perfect and everyones food will come out at once with a wave of the wand, like a 5 star Hogwarts.  We also do not PRETEND TO BE AS SUCH.We do also admittedly make mistakes. We also know that we are not going to please everyone))

I also wanted to take a minute and thank you for cursing and yelling at our FOH staff, who have absolute no control of how the food comes out or coursed. Hope you also enjoy the free take and bake cookies we sent home with you both parties. Just remember 325* fro 12-18 mins, or until done and golden brown. They are awesome,  Thank you so much for stopping in today. It was at least our pleasure to be able to serve you. CHEERS!!!!

reviews_data.review_text: Food, service & atmosphere are all fantastic! We sat outside on the patio to enjoy brunch on a beautiful fall day. Butternut squash tartine, Eggs Benedict, hamburger, home made chips, Spanish potatoes, cheese grits & oatmeal fruit bowl we're all super delicious!
5 stars across the board.
Great spot, but definitely order online or ahead of time. Place is understaffed and I was told 20 minutes. Waited a full hour. Everyone is friendly just has some room for improvement.

Holy moly this place is great. I had the Spanish omelet which was a bit more eggy than I've  had before but it was very very good.
I tried the boxty browns which are cabbage and potatoes and I would  say to definitely try those because they were great.
The best thing of the whole breakfast was the hot sauce. I recommend asking for it because it is amazing. I ate it on everything.
I didn't care much for the coffee not because it was bad but because it was fairly light and I like a dark roast.
I think I could eat here for every meal and never be disappointed.
Visited new Charlotte resident friends and this was on their list…I’m so glad I got to help them check it off and add to a regular list! The food and coffee was delicious!

I’ve been here many times and always give them the benefit of the doubt. Sadly I won’t be coming anymore. One of our ordered came out 15 minutes after the others. Bought sourdough loaf and it was molded the next morning. No thanks.

Took 40 minutes to get my husband's chicken and waffles, which was decent. It inexplicably took 11 more minutes to get my pancakes and scrambled eggs. The scrambled eggs had a weird texture, so I can't speak much to flavor. The pancakes were burned around the edges, and even after cutting that off, there will still crunchy spots. Flavor was fine, but not really any better than I'd make myself. The bacon was literally dripping with grease and left a puddle on the plate, I'm not even sure how they got that much on it. Not worth the almost $40 price tag. You also just have to wander around looking for street parking as there is none designated.
Food and service are good. Definitely check this place out.

So good! First time in and we’ll def be back. We had the Patatas Bravas with one over easy egg and the Spanish Omelette. Would recommend to get there early. Seats are limited. They do have outdoor seating available, but if it’s raining like today, best to get there early.
please eat here. it was delicious.
Love coming here. I’ve had their chorizo burrito and cuban sandwich, all really delicious. It has a comforting vibe, you can sit inside or outside. I’ll continue to return to try more items.
I'm writing this and haven't even finished my breakfast yet. I cant find the words to describe how incredible the food is. This is my new favorite place. 10/10!
The food and vibe were good.  We had to wait about 40 minutes for our food because they were short staffed, but we were told about the wait before we ordered.
Highly recommend this gem!!
This has to be the best food i have ever had.

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Dietary restrictions, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: The food was absolutely amazing! The pancakes were like no other!
Had the shrimp and grits. Very good, except a bit heavy on the kale. Overall good experience, though. My son had the chicken and waffles and it was really good, according to him.
Snickerdoodle cookie was salty and not great...BUT the BLT is unlike anything I've tasted before. Bread was delicious!
This a beautiful restaurant in the area. The food is great. At other tables all the dishes looked good. We enjoyed our brunch.  The hot sauce is phenomenal. The service is great. Thanks Chloe
Food was outstanding. Food is sometimes slow to come out but it is good enough to keep us coming back. If they were open later they would make an insane amount of business.  Is just so good.

Pretty disappointing experience, went here for brunch and waited over an hour at their wobbly ikea tables for two greasy chicken sandwiches with saltless fries. The floor is sticky and dirty and overall atmosphere is cluttered and unprofessional. You can get the same experience by getting roller hot dogs at a gas station, but at least then you know what you’re getting lol
Long wait for brunch but the service was considerate and kind, and the food was WORTH IT, SOOO good, I talk about local loaf all the time!

This perfectly decorated whole in the wall is the kind of place I wish were here where I live!! The food really surprises you with how good it is! 1st time here and was definitely pleasantly surprised!! When I'm in town this will definitely be the place I go too. Only need a tad bit newer outside tables, or maybe just pressure wash it and make a lil smoother. I know it may take away from the charm, but it'll help overall. 😉

Really great food and the “old man” there is the sweetest person. The baked goods look unassuming, but trust me they are all so good! The cookies are incredibly soft. This is a hidden gem definitely worth going back to. The only con is that food can take a while to come out, so only come if you’ve got the time to wait.
Staff was very friendly. Food was fairly quick for being made from scratch. Also the food was great would definitely recommend the English muffin.

Everything I’ve had from Local loaf has been delicious…. However they are very nearly always sold out of everything from the bakery by lunchtime, both during the week and over the weekend. Their fries are something else.

Run- don’t walk to Local Loaf for breakfast!  First time here today and we will def be back. It was a perfect mother/daughter breakfast treat. Such a cute, non assuming exterior in a great location.
We arrived right at 9:00 and ordered the baked apple grain bowl and the Chicken & The Egg.  Both were absolutely delicious and plated so nicely. Perfectly photogenic.
The steel cut oats were paired with just the right amount of fruit and sweetness.
The chicken….don’t get me started. DIVINE! That spicy sauce and perfectly poached egg on a tasty biscuit 💕
We will def make the drive back here (from Gastonia).  The friendly gentleman that took our order and served us was so kind.

Nice little place. Relaxed environment for brunch.  It was nice instead of the hustle bussle of some places. Good was good. I tried the pancakes.  They were a little sweet for me, but yummy with the apples inside.  Will go again to try something different. Took a bite of my friend's steak and harissa potatos....packed full of flavor! Very yummy...the lebna was a delightful balance with the harissa.

Local Loaf is always #1!!!
No CAP!!!
Food and service here are absolutely incredible, have worked my way through most of the menu and everything is insanely good. Best breakfast/ lunch spot I’ve been to bar none!
Food menu was amazing and food was great, got the savory bowl, only down side was i couldn't get a refill on coffee because the line to order was sooo long and they refilled at the counter
Amazing options and food.  The flavors and sauces are incredible.  The lobster roll and shrimp and grits are phenomenal and unique.
Best chicken and waffles ever!
Love this place!
The pancakes were awesome. I also got some of the chips and dip to go. I was very disappointed that for $8 it was a small amount of chips and a tiny thing of dip.
Very cute and quaint spot in a residential area. The food is delicious and the staff was very friendly. The have a Happy Hours Menu. I did the beets, potatoes and chips with dip. All phenomenal.

WOWZA - AWESOME - You have to try this place.  We ordered the Lobster Rolls, Cuban, Tenders Sandwich, Harissa Potatoes, Fried Mac n Cheese balls, BLT and Chicken n Waffles and without hesitation, each person said the best they ever had.  What a great neighborhood jem in NoDa.
Food is very salty. Got my order entirely wrong at first.
Lovely place with a great and delicious menu!

Local Loaf is exactly what you want from a small, local business. Chef Adam, Kristen and the entire staff serve amazing food in a friendly and relaxed atmosphere. And as an added bonus, they have the absolute best English muffins!!
Cool restaurant right in the middle of a neighborhood just blocks from Davidson Street. Picnic tables outside. Wasn't a fan of the Eggs Benedict, but was still a pleasant experience.
Very slow. Had to leave before we could even order. It just too small or understaffed.

Local Loaf has an adorable "mom and pop" vibe. It seemed extremely family oriented and homey.
The establishment itself is a repurposed house that turns into a restaurant. You order one of their delicious items at a reasonable price, grab you a seat, and patiently wait for it to be delivered. The serving sizes are enough for one person. There is limited seating, so be quick on your toes to find a spot. There is a good bit of vegetarian and vegan opitions. They serve tons of wine, so yes, you can have the mimosa at noon.

All and all, this is a nice place to grab a coffee, a fulfilling breakfast, or lunch with great hospitality.

We came for lunch while we were out and boy are we glad we did. We got the BLT, Burger, and kids tenders and we were all impressed by each of them. Lots of flavor in everything. The coffee was very tasty as well

The good reviews are clearly paid for and the bad ones lack details.
Absolutely disgusting; if you’re a lover of seasonless food and a pretty plate this is your spot.
Shrimp and grits- disgusting.
French toast- as expected; if you mess this up you shouldn’t be in the kitchen.
Grits- disgusting.
Bacon-overcooked. How? Local loaf made it possible.

Mimosas- 7/10 - wasn’t bad; but that’s it.

I’m genuinely concerned about everyone’s taste buds that actually enjoy this. It’s probably a medical condition.

Great local bakery turned into eclectic shop and So happy they brought back the Lobster Rolls!! Oh it’s so yummy and plenty of delicious Lobster in each bite!! I recommend getting two they are so great!! But could do one slider with a side and be full. The sourdough they use on their sandwiches has so much flavor and doesn’t tear the top out of your mouth….

As someone traveling through town, it seems that the reviews for this restaurant benefit from local adoration. With a waiting line stretching across the whole restaurant, you expect the food to be remarkable, and indeed, people in line were talking up how good certain items were.
The coffee cake muffin was one of those things where there were some bits of flavoring on the top of the muffin, then one scant strand of something in the middle, with the rest just straight muffin.
The breakfast burrito was like something you'd get from a college food service company, with all the components blending together into one mushy sort of non-flavor. There's no crispy from the tortilla or perhaps potato skin, no crunch from pepper or onion, no hints of seasoning that wake you up, no salsa on the side to punch it up - only the side of hot sauce helps this go down. I didn't eat the second half.
The service was about half the speed of a typical restaurant, but friendly.
Scrumptious! Quaint and locally owned breakfast and lunch spot. Unforgettable menu, with great beers and other drink offerings. We will definitely be back.

Visited Charlotte to see an old friend and we got a lovely breakfast here. You get to order quickly at a counter like any coffeeshop/cafe, but then staff will bring your food to your table for you. My sausage egg + cheese was huge and delicious, and the biscuit was absolutely wonderful. Really good vibes here, maybe a tad expensive but you get a good amount of food for your money.

GREAT staff, except for the beer Natzi girl.
Food is hit or miss.

Some of the best pancakes in Charlotte.
All the food I've had here so far is fantastic. One of my favorite restaurants in CLT so far.
Really good food, friendly service. Always enjoy the food,
Nice neighborhood spot. Pancakes are nice and crispy. They also have head-sized cookies. I took home the batter to make tonight.

Great food, cozy environment and a sweet older gentleman at the cash wrap!
We ordered the chicken and the egg!

Consistently some of the best food in Charlotte, and most comes at a great quality to value ratio. I eat here weekly and have never had a bad meal. Some favorites are their breakfast burrito, pancakes, and the chicken and waffles.
Very, very flavorful food. Sampled both eggs Benedict and breakfast burrito, and will return
The breakfast food here is great but be prepared to wait a long time. We'd eat here a lot more if wait times weren't so long.

I used to love this place when they were in 7th street market, but unfortunately not so much anymore. They changed up their menu and now they are super slow. Both times I went took forever to get the food, and on top of that, they are not handicapp accessible which was an issue for my daughter.
I’ve been here twice now for breakfast and the food HITS. Especially enjoyed the breakfast burrito.

Food is amazing!!! I placed an order for pick up for me and my staff (Btw the staff at Buffalo Eatz said the food was amazing!!!) and got a free coffee when I arrived and waited in the lobby. The atmosphere is beautiful, the coffee tasted great! The cookies are soft and good as hell!  The chicken and waffle were great! Can’t wait to try my falafel wrap… thanks definitely will be back!
When I tell you the Fiesta Cobb is by far one of THE BEST salads I have ever had…Delicious 😋

Worst take out breakfast I have ever had. The pancakes were mad dark, thick and gummy in the middle, super thin on the outside, and tasteless. Not sweet, salty or buttery. NOTHING. My eggs were ordered over medium and came super hard and salty. The bacon was the only thing that was barely cooked to edible standards. Lesson learned! Never again.
Great place in the neighborhood. Easy to walk to.
Bird & the egg is perfection. End of.

Mimosas and Spanish Migas is all that needs to be said. Amazingly flavorful food, I was blown away. The staff is pretty friendly and the gentleman at the register made me feel right at home and welcome to ask away. I appreciate the welcoming environment in addition to killer food. Though it's a little pricier to go regularly for the full sit down meal, I see myself going back for coffee and a pastry to enjoy more frequently. Cold brew was also fantastic!
I recommend the hot Italian sandwich

I'm planning on moving to Charlotte in the coming months and Local Loaf is just up the street from my office. I had the Chicken & the Egg, and I say this without any hesitation, that was the best piece of chicken I've ever had in my life. I understand that's an odd thing to say, but it was so perfectly seasoned, so perfectly cooked, and so perfectly crispy, it was just...perfect. on top of that my wife and I split an oatmeal cream pie for the nostalgia and it's so much better than I could've imagined. Oh, and I wish I caught her name but the girl at the counter with the piercings was so friendly and helpful. I can't wait to go back when I'm living there. I'm spreading the word to all my coworkers already there.
Great food and service with a fun relaxing atmosphere.
I’ve eaten here numerous times.  It’s crazy, welcoming, and the food is outstanding.  I ordered Thanksgiving sides to serve to my family.  And they raved about them.  👍🏻
Always excellent, professional, and friendly!!

This might be the first bad review I've ever written.  We can in on a weekend and the group of five before us brought this place to its knees. The older gentleman taking the orders slowly limps each order to the kitchen by himself. The coffee has effectively no refills. Maybe if you get back in the 35 minute line they'd do it, I'm not sure. The food was okay but wildly overpriced.

The people give you nasty looks when they delivered the food. The service was insanely slow. I thought maybe my food was ready and they didn't know who it belonged to so I asked if maybe there was a dish looking for its owner. They said they'd call my name. I asked how they'd know it, since they didn't ask me for it. They called me a conspiracy theorist and said it came from the credit card.

This place is the worst.
Wonderful place, to drink your coffee in a perfect silent place.

More than one eggshell in the Benedict. 😡

I get busy mornings, but that was too much eggshell.
We all enjoyed our lunch on a beautiful fall day in the neighborhood! Food was delicious, great experience!
Waited in line for 20 minutes to order food and the cook yelled take no more orders. So we left. Food looked otherwise good.

best chicken and waffles I've ever had! slightly spiced chicken with a great waffle (try it with the blueberry) and beautiful sauce.

I tried the protein egg and cheese English muffin another time and I wasn't super impressed, it was kinda greasy with honestly, too much under seasoned egg. but the chicken and waffles offsets this to warrant a 5 star ratingv
Had the chicken and blueberry waffle which was absolutely delicious. Mango mimosa was also very tasty.
Enjoyed myself and food was great. Will return again

I have driven by Local Loaf a few times in Charlotte NC and finally decided to try! Was so cute inside. There is no waitress service so you just order at the front and they bring your food to you. The place was super clean. They have wine by the bottle to purchase and they also had a great wine list by the glass. I had the French Sauvignon Blanc. The menu was amazing! It was so hard picking stuff but we had the sausage, egg and cheese sandwich, an order of fries, the fig and Brie toast and the bubble & squeak boxty benny but I substituted the salmon for prosciutto. Everything was so unbelievable. The fries were so crispy and well seasoned. The sandwich was huge and was delicious. I loved my Benny! Perfectly cooked and the fig and Brie combo was a perfect combo. I can’t wait to go back and try other things.

This was my first time at the local loaf. Everyone in my party ordered the chicken and (blueberry) waffles. This was definitely one of the best chicken and waffles I’ve ever had - even some of the best fried chicken I’ve had. The serving size was perfect, the food was exceptional and worth the price. Service was friendly, the wait wasn’t bad for Sunday brunch time, and the interior was clean and pleasant. Will definitely return!
Best egg and cheese sandwich I've had in Charlotte
Wonderful staff and amazing tamale! Unexpected.

Ordered take-out with my family. And came to Local Loaf with my toddler to pick up the food. They said they were running behind. When it was 30 minutes later than the online app said. I asked a waitress if it would be much longer because my son was getting restless.

The cook looked out the window and said 'Why don't you come back here and cook if you have a problem.". They then told me it would be in the next rotation. It has already been over an hour since I ordered. So would have likely been another 30 minutes before the order was ready. So I told the waitress (who was nice) could I have a refund because I didn't think my kid could wait for another 30 minutes (which would have been 90 minutes+ since I ordered). She sent me to the manager. Who sarcastically said - Anything you want. Then said it's done. I asked if I could have a receipt of the refund. He said Why Not? and handed it to me and walked away.

I understand a lot of places are short staffed but its no reason to be mean to the customers about it. It was a very disappointing trip.

I have enjoyed supporting this small business for a few years now. The lobster rolls, broccoli burger, grits, cucumber and tomato salad, breakfast burrito, and chicken and egg biscuit are always on point. They also have local products to enjoy such as honey, flavored syrups, specialty drinks and gourmet snacks. They adapted well during the pandemic.  The online ordering process is seamless and the food is consistently ready within the noted timeframe.
Inventive, delicious sandwiches and creative dishes.
They guys are very professional.
Awesome services.

spoke with them about a private event. seemed like they wanted to
help us but we did not receive promised email with pricing and menus and when we reached back out to them they were super rude an actually hung up
on me!  never never never going there !

We went mid morning on a Friday. We were the only table there. Staff was welcoming and friendly. Breakfast still took 20 minutes even though we were the only 2 orders. Food was amazing! Definitely understand why this place has huge waits on the weekend. Maybe a little more help in the kitchen would alleviate wait times? Definitely great food, ridiculous wait/serve times.
Service took around 30 minutes and our breakfast sandwiches were unmanageability big
Unassuming location, but an incredible breakfast. Not pictured: some of the best cheese grits in CLT.

I’m not one to leave bad reviews, but this place needs some serious TLC.
We called twice before coming in and received no response, so we decided to eat in. That was our biggest mistake. The floors are dirty, most tables are sticky, and the furniture is very wobbly and flimsy.

We waited for our food for over 30 minutes, had to go back to the cashier to ask for more water, and never received the salt and pepper we asked for.

The staff is very friendly and the food is absolutely delicious, but the severe understaffing and the dirtiness of the restaurant overshadowed the great meal we all had.

I do recommend this delicious food, but I suggest you order it to go (and hope they’ll pick up the phone to get your order).
The butternut squash toast was the highlight of everything we ordered
Great bagels
Great baked stuffs and one of the best breakfasts in NoDa. Impressive adult beverage selections too.

I'm not sure what the culture in Charlotte is to leave 4 stars after all positive comments, but it has effectively made the review process useless.  I just want to say this is some of the best food here.  Service was fantastic.  Could they use a little administrative help? Sure. But I'm rating the food, not the aesthetics or whether I can get tap water.  Food is 10/10.  Everything else is acceptable.

In town for Fam Reunion and found this hidden gem 15 mins from the hotel because all the breakfast spots near the hotel had an hr or more wait.  It's in a neighborhood and I was able to walk right in and order.  The ambiance is great and the elderly gentleman at the counter who took my order was very nice.  I ordered the Breakfast Burrito with a single pancake.  The Burrito was excellent but I forgot to get it without pork. The pancake tasted like cake and had a crunchy edge that made it even better.  I will say it is a lil pricey ($22 total) and the coffee was not very good. Oh, if they are busy, it may be hard to find parking.  But other than that, I will definitely come back the next time I'm in the Queen City.

Delicious food. I had the BLT with fried green tomatoes and white cheddar pimento cheese. The sandwich was so large I brought half home for the next day. Staff is friendly and welcoming. There are picnic tables outside. Some are shaded midday and it it's not too hot, it's nice to sit outside and have them bring your food to you.
Love the chicken & egg dish here
Lovely little place. The cookies Smack!
Excellent food! Ingredients were super fresh and the flavors were just perfect. The old man on counter was very friendly to chat with. Would be happy to visit again.
Cute local spot with the best pancakes in Charlotte!

A good friend of mine was in town last weekend and we decided to go to brunch that Sunday. I found a hidden gem off the beaten path in NODA. It's called the Local Loaf. It's very unpretentious and welcoming from the outside. Wooden picnic tables line the corner perimeter of the building. The inside isn't fancy either. Simple, spartan and comfortable. You'll find the menu online. No paper or laminated cards here. There was a gray haired gentleman taking orders and he was very friendly and knowledgable about the fare they offered. His name is Jay. So is mine. Anyhoo, there were only three people working...Jay, taking orders, one cook and a dynamite server who not only served, but helped the cook on the line. Jay told us that they had in excess of 30 call-in orders so it may be about 30 minutes before we would be served. We instantly liked this little place so much, we decided we didn't mind at all. Jay served us two cups of freshly brewed Smelly Cat coffee in rustic stoneware mugs and we quickly found an empty picnic table outside and settled in. My friend and I chit-chatted about everything and nothing as we are prone to do. Quaint little bungalow houses lined the streets of the intersection where the restaurant is located. We were in the shade and the fresh, hot cups of coffee fended off the lightest chill in the breeze. Our food finally arrived and the server, I forgot her name, placed it in front of us with a big smile on her face. We had a short friendly conversation and she left us to enjoy our brunch. And enjoyed it, we did! I ordered Croque Madam and it was everything. Brioche, nice salty, smoky ham, the morney and the cheese topped with the Sunnyside up egg. I lived in Montmartre, Paris and the Croque took me back to those days at Cafe Remy. Had my first of many there. I digress. My friend had light and fluffy waffles, bacon and overeasy eggs. She said for a simple meal, it was perfect. Cheers to the cook at Local Loaf! We will definitely come back. You don't come across little treasures that often.

Local Loaf is a must try neighborhood favorite! Awesome people and the food is always delicious, we’ve been coming for years! FRESH, local and unique! You can also find all sorts of interesting beverages and snacks outside of regular menu items!

So me and my significant other wanted to try a new place and found the site. So lets just say not what you expect. When a resteraunt is name local loaf your expecting fresh bread and organic orgredients. it looks like they wanted a wine bar and just throw food on the menu to sprose it up. The food is mediocre at best and not worth the price. It did not help hearing the cook complain about your order. I give it 2 stars because at least they tried with the over priced eggs and milk.

WELL WORTH THE WAIT!!! Yes, wait times are long, so if you’re looking for a quick in and out, this might not be the place for you. But these aren’t big batch meals, they’re made individually as orders come in - which is what makes it so incredibly delicious! If you’re looking for some of the tastiest, highest quality food, I can’t more highly recommend the Local Loaf.  My meal (the Spanish migas) legitimately was some of the best food I’ve ever had in Charlotte. We will be back!!!!!

Waited over an hour for a sausage egg and cheese on a bagel… they told me 30 minutes but come on. You are not even that busy - how does it take this long to make such a simple menu item?  Cool spot in the middle of a neighborhood though.
Cozy little place. Loved the food.
Avocado toast not very pleasant from this place :/ staff was cool tho

This place is amazing!
Kristin and Adam know how to run a business where they put the customer first.

I’m tired of run of the mill breakfast places like Dunkin and this is my new breakfast spot!

Fan-freaking-Tastic food. No real table service which is pretty nice honestly, and is probably what makes such delicious food so much more affordable. 25 minute wait, but we were forewarned and it was completely worth it. Great staff too!!!! If i ever go back to the area, it'll definitely be a stop for brunch again. Hands down.👏👏👏👏

Very friendly and cozy neighbourhood bakery👏 if you pass through NoDa, definitely grab some breakfast bagels from this place. They also have a small shop where you can buy their locally sourced products 👍

This is one of my favorite places to eat in charlotte hands down. Their food is absolutely delicious. Good quality and fresh. The staff is super friendly and they have house baked goods, wine, beer, and other drinks to chose from even if you’re not eating. The shrimp and grits is the best, shrimp and grits are one of my favorite meals  to get anywhere I go, and this is top 2. Please go and eat it right now.
Very cool place, sausage egg sandwich and chicken waffles were probably the best we've tried anywhere.

Delicious, high quality food with cute dining. It wasn't too busy when we stopped by, but still had to wait almost 30 minutes for a To-Go order. Still, it was worth it in the end. Killer Sunday morning spot.
It's one thing to just be a great bakery. It's another to be a great bakery that also knows how to showcase their breads with mouthwatering sandwiches.

The layout is nice.. but we waited 1 and 1/2 for food and it wasn't even that good . Nobody greets you when you come or even helps you. We sat at the table for 20 minutes before we even figured out that we had to order a different way.. this was our 1st and last time eating here.. if you could leave 0 stars i would
I so LOVE this place. It is a calm atmosphere. It's home away from home. Their chicken & waffles are to die for! 😋

Incredible food. And what lovely people.
I would recommend this place.
Amazing food. One of the very best brunch menus in Charlotte. While there is dining inside, ambiance is lacking a bit. Fun to eat at the picnic tables outside or to take home.

Waited an hour and ten minutes for eggs and a fruit cup…. Staff is inefficient. Lady at front counter standing around drinking coffee, meanwhile they run out of coffee for their actual paying customers. Food runner brings out orders and sits them on the shelf and no one is calling names. Many other customers standing around wondering where their food is because the staff isn’t communicating what is going on. Seems like no one cares about their job. I really wanted to give this place a chance, but so many improvements could be made. This place is mismanaged and it’s unfortunate. I walked out and am disputing the charges with my credit card.

We arrived at the Local Loaf around 9:45am and ordered our food. Literally been an hour and our food hasn't been ready yet. We ordered 2 breakfast items. Lady up front with pigtails seem like she doesn't know what she's doing or is tired. The runner is bringing to-go orders out but isn't calling names. Super inefficient the way it is run here. We ended up leaving with no food after over an hour of waiting for TWO BREAKFAST items. Spent $45 for two breakfast items, 2 drip coffees, and a bowl of fruit. Now I have to dispute the charges through my bank. First time and last time coming here.

Great food, slow service. Build in lots of time because it takes a while for the food most times - I've been waiting an hour for my food as I type this even after ordering ahead. Food is usually worth the wait, but it's definitely a drag on the overall experience as other reviewers have attested to.
Simply AMAZING!!! I couldn't ask for a better experience. They say a way to a man Heart is through his stomach in let me tell you they got my heart ❤️.

Best shrimp and grits I’ve had in years (coming from a former New Orleanian).  We also had butternut squash tartine and beet salad - Both were so good and were made with with fresh, healthy ingredients.

Overall: Food was timely, beer was delicious, neighborhood was cool, music was good, and the team was very friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend!!

Omg... Awesome neighborhood breakfast joint! All locally sourced produce. Plus they make their own, bread baked goods, cookies, and make it all fresh. I got there when the cookies came out of the oven. O boy... Next time I'm taking them home to bake. Wonderful experience for me... P. S The pancake is crispy around the edges. This guy has been making pancakes since he was 7...there good!
